    "name": "Requirements Engineer & Developer - Digital Microscopy (m/f/d)",
    "company_name": "EVIDENT Europe GmbH",
    "location": "Münster",
    "remote": "On-site",
    "location_lat": 51.96236,
    "location_lon": 7.62571,
    "description": "Evident Technology Center Europe GmbH (ETCE), based in Münster, Germany, has been developing and producing intelligent software and hardware solutions for microscopy as a global \"Center of Excellence\" for over 35 years. Originally, ETCE was part of Olympus Corporation. Olympus spun off the business unit in April 2022 and transferred the business activities of its Scientific Solutions division to the newly founded, independent company Evident. Headquartered in Tokyo, Japan, Evident employs around 4,500 people at a total of 57 locations worldwide, where it develops, produces and distributes Olympus brand products and is constantly expanding its product portfolio. Evident offers a wide range of microscopy systems for clinical diagnostics, life science research and industrial applications. In addition, Evident develops and produces videoscopes, products for non-destructive material testing and devices for X-ray fluorescence analysis. You will join an experienced agile development team working on the SLIDEVIEW VS200, a high-end automated slide-scanning and digital microscopy system used in life-science research and medical diagnostics (IVD). This position combines classic requirements engineering with hands-on software development. You will analyze and document technical requirements – and independently deliver new functionality into our products. Within the Scrum team, you act as both a bridge builder and an active contributor to the software. Tasks Eliciting, analyzing, and documenting requirements for software solutions in the field of life-science research and medical diagnostics Translating domain requirements into user stories and acceptance criteria, and maintaining the product backlog together with the Product Owner Acting as the interface between scientists, application specialists, and software developers Independently implementing product functionality within the Scrum team – from requirement to finished feature Close technical collaboration with the development team throughout the entire implementation process Active participation in Scrum sprints including Sprint Planning, Daily Standup, Review, and Retrospective Creating and maintaining technical documentation and interface specifications Requirements Degree in natural science, computer science, or a related field Experience in requirements engineering or a comparable bridging role between domain and software development IREB Certified Professional for Requirements Engineering (CPRE) certification is desirable Programming skills ideally in C++, C#, or Rust – you actively contribute functionality to our products Familiarity with agile methods, ideally with hands-on Scrum experience Strong analytical mindset and the ability to translate complex scientific topics into precise software requirements Very good English and good German language skills Benefits Flexible working hours, incl. mobile work 30 days of holiday time each year 13 salaries a year Regular training courses Extensive company pension scheme Job bike Preventive healthcare, free beverages &#x26; fresh fruit and vegetables daily Joint company events and activities Interesting, diversified field of activity in an international working environment Evident Europe GmbH is an equal opportunities employer and we look forward to receiving your application. Find more English Speaking Jobs in Germany on Arbeitnow",
